Detailed Description

Request to add a route to the route storage.

After the normal RequestPacket header the request packet contains: {tabular}{lll} Pos & Size & Destription \ REQUEST_HEADER_SIZE & 4 bytes & RouteID \ +4 & 4 bytes & UIN \ +8 & 4 bytes & validUntil \ +12 & 4 bytes & createTime \ +16 & 4 bytes & originLat \ +20 & 4 bytes & destinationLat \ +20 & 4 bytes & originLon \ +24 & 4 bytes & destinationLon \ +28 & 4 bytes & originMapID \ +32 & 4 bytes & destinationMapID \ +36 & 4 bytes & originItemID \ +40 & 4 bytes & destinationItemID \ +44 & 2 bytes & originOffset \ +46 & 2 bytes & destinationOffset \ +48 & 4 bytes & flags, isReRoute \ +52 & 4 bytes & routePack->getLength \ +56 & 2 bytes & strlen extraUserinfo \ +58 & 2 bytes & originAngle \ +60 & 4 bytes & driverPref size \ +64 & 4 bytes & urmask size \ +68 & extraUserinfo bytes & extraUserinfo \ & routePack bytes & routePack \ & driverPref bytes & driverPref \ & urmask size & urmask \ {tabular}

Parameters:
routePack The route to store.
UIN The user of the route.
extraUserinfo Extra information about the user. Things like "Navigatoraddress=46708111111&Navigatorid=6" may be usefull.
validUntil Time when route can be considered "old" in UTC. Usually (currentTime + Total time in route)*N where N is safetyfactor.
createTime The time, in UTC, when the route was created. Used to determine if the route contains current mc2-maps.
originLat The latitude of the route's origin.
originLon The longitude of the route's origin.
originAngle The angle of the route's origin.
originMapID The mapID of the route's origin.
originItemID The itemID of the route's origin.
originOffset The offset of the route's origin.
destinationLat The latitude of the route's destination.
destinationLon The longitude of the route's destination.
destinationMapID The mapID of the route's destination.
destinationItemID The itemID of the route's destination.
destinationOffset The offset of the route's destination.
driverPref The settings for the route.
urmask The urmask used for the route.
isReRoute If this is a reroute using route storage coords.
